# Privacy Policy — DCB Test App

**Last updated: April 2026**

## Overview

DCB Test App is an internal test application developed and operated by 
Allan Rist for the purpose of verifying Direct Carrier Billing (DCB) 
integrations with Google Play.

This app is not intended for use by the general public. 

## Data Collection

DCB Test App does not collect, store, or transmit any personal data. 
The app does not include analytics, advertising SDKs, or any third-party 
data collection tools.

## Purchases

In-app purchases and subscription flows are handled entirely by Google 
Play Billing. Any payment data is processed by Google and the relevant 
carrier. Boku does not receive or store payment information through this 
application.

## Device Permissions

The app requires the following permission:

- **BILLING** — required to initiate Google Play purchase flows for 
testing purposes

No other device permissions are requested.

## Third Parties

The only third-party service used is Google Play Billing, which is 
governed by Google's own privacy policy at 
https://policies.google.com/privacy

## Contact

For questions about this application, contact the Boku integration team 
at google@boku.com

## Changes

As this is a test tool, this policy may be updated without 
notice. The last updated date at the top of this page reflects the most 
recent revision.
